# Real Estate AI Sales Dashboard

This plan outlines the development of a real estate application designed to help agents and owners ("Harsh") track and summarize customer interactions using AI, specifically focusing on maximizing property value through bid tracking.

## Business Problem
Field agents and sales representatives speak with leads to negotiate property deals. Currently, the owner lacks a centralized way to understand how these conversations are going. More importantly, when multiple agents are showing the **same property** to different clients, there is no centralized track of who has offered what amount. The owner misses out on leveraging multiple interested parties to increase the final sale price (bidding).

## Proposed Solution
A web application with the following core functionalities:
1. **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)**: Two primary roles — `Agent` (Field/Sales Rep) and `Owner` (Broker/Admin, "Harsh").
2. **Agent Workflow**:
   - Log in to the application.
   - Select a specific **Property** they are showing.
   - Upload audio recordings of conversations with customers.
   - Fill out lead details: Client Name, Phone Number, and **Offered Amount / Bid**.
3. **AI Processing Pipeline**:
   - Extract text from uploaded audio (Transcription).
   - Generate a structured summary of the conversation.
   - Automatically determine **Client Interest Level** (Interested, Not Interested) and highlight any pricing discussions.
4. **Owner Dashboard**:
   - **Global Leads View**: View all agents' activities and leads.
   - **Property Hub (Bidding Tracker)**: A view for each property showing a ranked list of all clients who have seen it, their respective agents, their bid amounts, and their interest level. 
   - When a property is about to close, the owner can instantly see other high-bidders and reach out to say, "The property is about to sell, are you willing to increase your offer?"

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review the updated architecture and the "Open Questions" section below, as your feedback will guide the technical choices before we start writing code.

## Proposed Architecture & Tech Stack

### Frontend & Backend Framework
- **Next.js (App Router)**: A full-stack React framework that allows us to build a beautiful frontend and powerful backend API routes in one codebase.
- **Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui**: For a modern, fast, and premium broker/agent dashboard experience.

### Database, Auth & Storage
- **Firebase**: Quick setup for Authentication, Firestore (Database), and Firebase Storage (for securely uploading and storing audio files).

### AI Integration
- **OpenAI API**:
  - `Whisper-1`: For transcribing the audio files accurately.
  - `GPT-4o` (or GPT-4o-mini): For analyzing the transcript and returning structured JSON (Summary, Interest Level, Objections).

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Initial Setup
#### [NEW] `package.json` & Next.js config
- Initialize the Next.js project with TailwindCSS.
- Install Firebase & OpenAI SDKs.

### 2. Data Layer (Firestore Collections)
#### [NEW] `models`
- **Users**: Agents & Owner.
- **Properties**: Name, Location, Asking Price, Status (Active/Sold).
- **Leads/Bids**: Associated Property, Associated Agent, Client Name, Client Phone, Offered Amount, Audio File URL, AI Transcript, AI Summary, Interest Level.

### 3. User Interface Components
#### [NEW] `app/login/page.js`
- Entry point for both Owner and Agents to sign in.
#### [NEW] `app/agent/dashboard/page.js`
- Agent view to list their submitted leads and an action to add new ones.
#### [NEW] `app/agent/upload/page.js`
- Dropdown to **select Property**.
- Inputs for Client Name, Phone, **Offered Amount**.
- File dropzone to upload the audio recording.
#### [NEW] `app/owner/dashboard/page.js`
- Harsh's overview. Stats on properties, total active leads, and recent activities.
#### [NEW] `app/owner/property/[id]/page.js`
- **The Bidding Hub**: Detailed view for a specific property. Shows a table: `Agent | Client | Offered Amount | AI Interest Level | AI Summary`. This allows Harsh to easily spot the highest bidders before closing a sale.

### 4. API & AI Processing
#### [NEW] `app/api/process-audio/route.js`
- Secure route that receives the uploaded audio, transcribes it via Whisper, extracts insights via GPT (including Interest Level), and saves the row to Firestore.

